        <num>CCRP 227.1</num>
        <heading>227.1.  Prevention of escape; use of force</heading>
        <content>
          <p>Art. 227.1.  Prevention of escape; use of force
A guard or other law enforcement officer is justified in the reasonable use of force, to prevent the escape from a state correctional facility, parish prison, or the physical custody of a guard or other law enforcement officer of a person under sentence or awaiting trial.</p>
        </content>
